  <section class="content-block p-0 ">
    <div class="vlx-container pb-0">
      <div>
        <div class="lg:text-xl uppercase font-bold mb-3">Jury statement</div>
        <div class="text-editor">
          <p>Rarely is daylight used so consistently in multi-storey residential construction as in this renovation project, whose radicality only becomes apparent when looking inside. With great artistry, the architects have taken on an apartment building that had no façade openings on the south side.</p>
<p>Externally, the renovation is characterized by understatement. It reinforces the historical qualities of the stock instead of concealing them. Inside, only a few additional skylights create diverse and surprising lighting situations. The building openings themselves remain hidden from view – the focus of the concept is on indirect light and grazing light, which cleverly stages the spatial contours.</p>
<p>Vertical connections across several levels make the apartments appear larger than they actually are. Again and again, wall and ceiling openings open visual axes even in unusual places and arouse curiosity about the origin of daylight.</p><p><br /><br /> </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

